    type="FAQPage"
    data={[
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the best AI website builder for musicians?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "For solo musicians and singer-songwriters, Mixo ($9/month) is the best choice with affordable pricing, music player embeds, bio and photo galleries, and easy gig listing capabilities. Squarespace works well for bands wanting professional presentation with member profiles, tour date calendars, and merchandise integration. Framer is ideal for DJs and producers wanting modern aesthetic (9.5/10) with audio embeds and portfolio-quality showcase. Wix offers good features for music teachers needing booking forms, lesson scheduling, and payment processing. Bandzoogle is a dedicated music platform worth considering but is more expensive. For most musicians, prioritize: embedded music players, tour/event calendar, bio and photos, contact/booking info, social media links, and mobile optimization for streaming on phones."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do musicians need custom websites or are AI builders sufficient?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "AI website builders are absolutely sufficient for most musicians. Modern AI builders create professional music websites with embedded audio players, photo galleries, tour dates, merchandise stores, and all key features. All major streaming platforms (Spotify, SoundCloud, YouTube, Apple Music) provide embed codes that work perfectly with AI builders. Consider custom development only if you have: very specific technical requirements, need complex membership systems, want unique interactive features, or have substantial budget. For 95% of musicians, AI builders create professional, effective websites at a fraction of the cost and time. Your fans care about your music and easy access to it, not website technology. Focus on great embeds, clear contact info, and mobile optimization."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What features should musician websites include?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Musician websites need: Embedded music player - Spotify, SoundCloud, or custom player above fold. High-quality photos - press shots, band photos, live performance shots. Bio/about section telling your story and musical style. Tour dates or upcoming shows calendar with ticket links. Contact/booking information for venues and promoters. Social media links - Spotify, Instagram, YouTube, TikTok. Music videos or live performance footage. Merchandise store or links to Bandcamp/store. Press kit section for media and venues. Newsletter signup to build your fanbase. Mobile optimization - many fans listen on phones. key: music accessible, contact clear, mobile optimized."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Should I auto-play music on my website?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
