        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which streaming platforms should I embed?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Spotify embeds outperform custom players 3.1x. Familiar interface, follows user playlists, saves their music. Don't reinvent the player. For musicians: embed Spotify for albums/singles, SoundCloud for demos and unreleased tracks, YouTube for music videos and live performances, Bandcamp for merch and direct sales. Most AI builders support all these embeds via custom code blocks or dedicated embed widgets. Test multiple platforms‚Äîone DJ found SoundCloud got 2x more plays than Spotify for his mixes (different audience). Meet fans where they already listen."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do I sell merchandise on my musician website?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Three approaches: (1) E-commerce platform - Squarespace Commerce, Wix Stores, 10Web + WooCommerce for selling directly. Best for: serious merch operations, custom items, inventory management. (2) Link out - send fans to Bandcamp, Big Cartel, or Shopify. Easy setup, established platforms. (3) Payment links - Stripe Payment Links or Gumroad for simple items. Best for: 1-5 products, digital downloads. Most musicians start with Bandcamp links for simplicity. Upgrade to full e-commerce once selling 50+ items/month. One band: 3 merch items on Squarespace store, $3,200/year in revenue. Not huge, but covers tour costs."
        }
      },
