          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Display upcoming shows first (reverse chronological). Band A: chronological with past shows first = few booking inquiries. Band B: upcoming shows only, past shows archived = 2.7x more bookings. Promoters care about upcoming availability, not history. For each show: date, venue name, city/state, ticket link, door time, age restriction. Link to ticketing platform (Ticketmaster, Eventbrite) or 'Contact for booking' for private events. One test: added 'Book this date' button to each empty date slot. Got 3 inquiries first month from venues checking availability. Make your calendar work for you, not just display information."
